Subject: Re: [T2] Ball joint removal

Its important to get it to a dull red, NOT a bright red. The ball
joints will pop out with a good whack when the arms are dull. a *good*
whack.

This is ok because the torsion arms are heat treated steel. getting it
hot to a bright red may cause problems.

Eddie


> The main point was heating the torsion arm around the ball joint to a bright
> red and using a large hammer (BFH) on the side of the torsion arm portion
> encompassing the ball joint.
